race.comment: TEQUILA BABY (13) built on her near miss first-up at Kembla with a dogged win over this distance at Canterbury last start. Eye-balled the leader that day then was strong too late. Honest mare who recorded a big win at her only third-up run so there is still more to come from her. QUIETLY ARROGANT (8) last appeared when down the track in Listed company in June. Beaten narrowly by Rivellino as a juvenile at Group 2 level so if Snowden has her back on track she can fully test this field. REMEMBER JACK (14) flashed home but missed in a photo when fresh from a seven-week let-up recently over 1100m at Canterbury. Hasn't won for a long while but that last run suggests the drought is close to its end. The lightly raced PEACE CENTRE (6) resumed with a sound third behind the in-form Crepe Myrtle over 1100m at Canterbury a fortnight ago. Won second-up last prep off the same first-up figure. Right in the mix. LIVIN' THING (3) has won two from two when fresh so must be respected first-up.
